- @{b}SAS Institute@{ub} for their great SAS/C C compiler
- @{b}Commodore@{ub} for the AMIGA
- Everyone I have forgotten now
@endnode



@node installation "Installation"

You need OS 2.04 or higher to run PlusEd. I have started developing PlusEd
on an A500 with OS2.0 and later on I switched to an A4000 with OS3.0. It
has been tested on an A500, A1200, A2000 and A4000 with OS 2.04, 2.05,
2.1 and 3.0 and it worked well with all configurations.

The installation for @{b}OS2.1 or higher@{ub} is simple. Just start the appropriate
installation script and answer the questions. If you are still using @{b}OS2.04@{ub}
you have to copy PlusEd just where you want it and to install the IBM.font
in fonts: and the @{"ReqTools.library" link reqtools} in libs:.
It is not possible to run PlusEd in any other language than English below
OS 2.1.

The file 'PlusEd.030' is a PlusEd version which is optimized for 68030
processors. It will crash on processors below 68020 !
@endnode



