@node project "Project"

The 'Project' menu holds functions that affect your whole document or PlusEd
itself :

@{b}Clear...@{ub}

Well, that should be clear :-)

@{b}Open...@{ub}

Er... Nothing much to say, either.

@{b}Save@{ub}

Saves the document in a highly opzimized ANSI code under its old name.

@{b}Save as...@{ub}

Saves the document under a new name.

@{b}Special save...@{ub}

Here comes something special : Many BBS programs and so-called ANSI readers
can't handle PlusEd's output, though it is totally standard !
Most programs have problems with switching off the styles separately.
You should then use 'Save with ESC [0m...'. Other programs need their texts
with CR+LF at the end of a line. Save the files for these programs with
'Save with CR+LF...'. And some programs (e.g. the MultiAmnet® BBS software)
require both ('Save with CR+LF and ESC [0m...').

And then there is the menu item 'Save as ASCII...'. This one's for saving
plain ASCII texts without any ANSI sequences.

@{b}About...@{ub}

Gives you information about PlusEd and the registered user of this version.

@{b}Help...@{ub}

Displays a help window with the keyboard shortcuts.

@{b}Quit...@{ub}

Hasta la vista, baby...
@endnode



@node edit "Edit"

@{b}Redraw screen@{ub}

This is useful if PlusEd produces some trash in the text. It has never
happened, but I've added it just to be on the safe side.

@{b}Repeat character@{ub}

Repeats the last character that you've inserted into the text (by typing it
on the keyboard or by selecting it in the @{"symbol gadgets" link symgads}.

@{b}Copy line from above@{ub}

Copies the line above the cursor to the current line. Behaviour depends on
@{"Insert/Overwrite" link overwrite} mode !

@{b}Enter ASCII...@{ub}

Enter an ASCII character by typing in its number.

@{b}Delete line@{ub}

Deletes the current line. Behaviour depends on @{"Insert/Overwrite" link overwrite} mode !

@{b}Insert line@{ub}

Inserts an empty line at the current position.

@{b}Delete to EOL@{ub}

Deletes the current line from the cursor position to the right border.

@{b}Draw box@{ub}
@{b}Draw line@{ub}

Draws a box/line, either with the IBM graphics characters (single & double),
with plain ASCII characters or with a user-defined character ('Select...').
If @{"Overwrite" link overwrite} mode is deactivated, overlapping lines/boxes will be handled
correctly by replacing the characters at the connection points. If you want
wo draw a line/box "above" an other one, you should activate @{"Overwrite" link overwrite}.

@{b}Quickwrite...@{ub}

This is one of the most impressive functions of PlusEd. You can select one
of the fonts in the Quickwrite window and enter a text. This text will then
be inserted at the current cursor position, written in the selected font.
It is even possible to work with Insert mode (turn @{"Overwrite" link overwrite} off).
@endnode



@node block "Block"

This menu holds functions which affect the marked block :

@{b}Mark block@{ub}

After selecting this item, you can mark the block with the left mouse button
or F3. You can use F4 to cancel this operation. F3 and F4 are always used
in PlusEd to select positions and to cancel an operation.

@{b}Insert block@{ub}

Inserts the block at the current cursor position. Behaviour depends on
@{"Insert/Overwrite" link overwrite} mode !

@{b}Make 3D@{ub}
@{b}Make shadows@{ub}

Two nice effects. Just trie them out with some huge letters.

@{b}Set current colors@{ub}
@{b}Set current styles@{ub}

Uses the current colors/styles for the entire block.

@{b}Exchange colors...@{ub}

Exchanges two colors within the block.

@{b}Replace color...@{ub}

Replaces one color in the block by an other one.

@{b}Replace character...@{ub}

Replaces one character in the block by an other one.
@endnode



@node pen "Selecting a pen"

You can use the 'Pen' menu or the pen gadgets to select a pen. This pen
will be used for text that you are writing and for funtions like "Use the
current colors for the selected block".
@endnode



@node paper "Selecting a paper color"

You can use the 'Paper' menu or the paper gadgets to select a paper color.
This paper color will be used for the background of text that you are
writing and for funtions like "Use the current colors for the selected
block".
@endnode



@node mode "Mode"

This menu holds keyboard shortcuts for the @{"style & text" link styletext}, the @{"directions" link directions}
and the @{"overwrite" link overwrite} gadgets.
@endnode



@node style "Style"

You can select the style (Bold, Italics, Underlined) or reset it (Plain) in
the "Style" menu and style gadgets.
@endnode



@node symgads "Symbol gadgets"

If you click on a symbol gadget, a graphics character will be inserted at
the current cursor position just as if you typed it in via the keyboard.
@endnode



@node styletext "Style & Text"

If the style gadget is activated, all actions which manipulate the text
(writing, QuickWrite, copying,...) will change the colors and styles.

If the text gadget is activated, all actions will change the characters.

All this may sound a bit complicated, but it isn't. Some examples :
- Set 'Text' and clear 'Style' if you want to change some text and don't
  alter the colors and styles, because the text is in a beautiful ANSI
  painting.
- Set 'Style' and clear 'Text' if you want to add colors and styles to
  plain ASCII texts.
You should switch @{"Overwrite" link overwrite} on for both examples.
@endnode



@node directions "Directions"

You can chose the directions for the cursor movement in the 'Mode' menu
and with the direction gadgets.
@endnode



@node overwrite "Overwrite"

If Overwrite is activated, everything which is inserted into the text
(typed in, copied,...) will overwrite the things at the current position.
If Overwrite is not activated (also called 'Insert mode'), the text at
the current cursor position will be moved to the right when new text is
inserted.

You can select Insert/Overwrite in the 'Mode' menu and with the 'Overwrite'
gadget.
@endnode



@node prefs "Preferences"

You can chose between IBM.font and Topaz.font for the text diplay. You can
set the TAB size for TABs in texts which you are loading. You can alter
the colors or chose between several presets.

If you save the prefs 'Volatile' they will be gone when you reset your
Amiga. If you want to keep them, you have to save them as 'Permanent'.
@endnode



@node registering "Registering PlusEd"

PlusEd is a so-called @{b}Shareware program@{ub}. You may test it, before you buy it.
I.e. in the case of PlusEd : The 'Save' functions are disabled in evaluation
versions, so that you can test everything, but you can't use it normally.
I've included some examples to show you the quality of PlusEd's save
funtions. (The examples are mainly pictures from BBSs. Beware ! The
'PLUS'-BBS is currently offline. So don't call it. It will be online again
around spring or summer 1993.)

If you want to get a full version of PlusEd (including 'Save' functions),
you have to register. You will then get a keyfile which will 'unlock' your
version of PlusEd. If you register you also have the possibility to get help
with PlusEd via EMail (see below for EMail addresses).

The registration fee is @{b}DM 30@{ub} or @{b}US$ 20@{ub}. Please send this money together
with the filled-in @{"registration form" link "registration form/main"} (included in the file 'Registration
form') directly to the author (me). If you want to register via EMail,
please tranfer the money (in DM, please !) to Stefan Zeiger, Account Nr.
240847285, Sparkasse Aschaffenburg-Alzenau (Routing code 795-500-00),
with the comment "PlusEd", and send the registration form to one of my EMail
addresses.

The use and distribution of PlusEd is restricted by the ! Wizard Works !
Program License, Version 3, which is included in this distribution in the
file '@{"License" link "license/main"}'.

